This paper is primarily focused on game theory and mechanism design, which suggests that cs.GT (Game Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with auctions, which is a common topic in cs.EC (Economics and Computation). The use of iterated elimination of weakly dominated strategies suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), as these are common techniques in those fields. Finally, the paper involves analyzing the efficiency of algorithms, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
